Gekkeikan Horin Daiginjo Sake
Horin Daiginjo Sake is
considered by Japanese connoisseurs as
the ultra-premium rice wine. It is made from two specially
selected rice varieties, "Yamada Nishiki" and "Gohyakumangoku,"
which are cultivated especially for brewing. The Gekkeikan Sake
Company in Kyoto is well known around the world as
one of the leading Japanese sake vintners.
DESSERT
WINE
• 1?
Graham's Vintage Port
W. & J. Graham & Co. has, since 1820,
become one of the most prestigious names in fine port wines.
Careful decanting results in a brilliantly clear, sweet, ruby-red
dessert wine. Vintage Port is boldly aromatic and flavorful
with rich tones of brambleberries and plums-
matured with time to a satin texture.

DINNER
We are pleased to offer a variety of dining options.
You may select our Western Dinner,
our traditional Japanese Dinner, listed on page 7,
the Lighter Fare service, where your entree is created from the Salad Cart,
or our Dine Upon Request® option,
a complete meal presented all at once, whenever you prefer.
Should you choose our Dine Upon Request option
and wish to dine as soon as possible, please notify your Flight Attendant.
